The paper focuses on the issue of data loss in Android apps, which is a software engineering problem (cs.SE). The paper also discusses the need for explicit implementation of state-saving logic, which is related to programming languages and compilers (cs.PL). The benchmark presented in the paper is a collection of faulty apps, which can be seen as a software development dataset (cs.SD). The paper also discusses the usability issues and unexpected crashes caused by data loss, which is related to human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Finally, the paper specifically focuses on Android apps, which falls under the mobile computing category (cs.MOBILE).
